<p><b><a name="what_is_thyroid_peroxidase" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/thyroid_pictures_slideshow/article.htm" rel="slide" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">Thyroid</a> peroxidase (TPO) is an enzyme made in the <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/thyroid_quiz/quiz.htm" rel="quiz" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">thyroid</a> gland that is important in the production of <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/hyperthyroidism_pictures_slideshow/article.htm" rel="slide" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">thyroid hormone</a>. TPO is found in thyroid follicle cells where it converts the thyroid hormone T4 to T3.</p>.<p>The thyroid gland is located in the lower part of the neck, below the Adam's apple, wrapped around the trachea (windpipe). </p>.<p><b><a name="what_is_the_thyroid_peroxidase_test" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>Thyroid peroxidase test is a test that measures the level of an antibody that is directed against thyroid peroxidase (TPO). </p>.<p>Autoantibodies to thyroid peroxidase (TPOAb) are produced within the body. The presence of TPOAb in the blood reflects a prior attack on the thyroid tissue by the body's immune system. <span id="cntid"></span></p>.<p><b><a name="what_does_a_positive_thyroid_peroxidase_test_mean" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="what_are_other_names_for_thyroid_peroxidase_test" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>This test goes by a confusing number of names, including:</p>.<p>Previous contributing author: Frederick Hecht, MD, FAAP<span id="cntid"></span></p>